result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyjuan D Ford was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tyjuan D Ford is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tyjuan D Ford was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Tyjuan D Ford was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
CONDITIONS AS TO BOTH COUNTS:
Successfully complete "Batterers intervention" counseling and continue programming. Successfully complete any other counseling and/or treatment deemed appropriate.
Mental Health Evaluation and take all prescribed medications.
Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment. Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol. No contact with victim, Tiffanie N. without prior approval of the court.
Obtain and maintain employment and or school (full-time).

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs. Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges, victim/witness surcharge, the domestic violence surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections, during period of probation or CIVIL JUDGMENT. Cash bail to apply from case 2014CF1213.

No firearms; weapons. Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
